         <abstract>
            <label>ABSTRACT</label>
            <p>This paper describes a method to estimate the engine stop position using any production style crank position sensor, while accounting for possible engine rock-back. The approach is based on modeling the engine speed state, achieving robustness and ease of calibration by adapting the rubbing friction model component during the first part of engine coast-down, followed by open-loop modeling when the engine speed has dropped below the sensor signal validity threshold.</p>
         </abstract>
